# This file intentionally left blank.
#
# Next.js serves files from `public/` at the root of the web server,
# and the Dockerfile's standalone COPY step expects this directory to
# exist. The project currently has no static assets to serve from here
# (icons/fonts/etc are either baked into the bundle or loaded from
# external URLs), so this .gitkeep exists purely to ensure the
# directory is committed and the Docker build can `COPY /app/public`
# without failing.
#
# When you add a static asset (favicon, logo, og:image), drop it in
# this directory and reference it from your components as `/filename`.
